item.description: 1.66.0 # Unreleased Will be stable on: 15 December, 2022 Will branch from master on: 28 October, 2022 Neither require nor imply lifetime bounds on opaque type for well formedness Fix #[derive(Default)] on a generic #[default] enum adding unnecessary Default bounds Stabilize #![feature(mixed_integer_ops)] Bump Unicode to version 15.0.0, regenerate tables Make the c feature for compiler-builtins an explicit opt-in Update unicode-rs crates to Unicode 15 Stabilize bench_black_box

1.65.0 # Unreleased Will be stable on: 3 November, 2022 Will branch from master on: 16 September, 2022 Tracking issue for RFC 2046, label-break-value Stabilize let else Use niche-filling optimization even when multiple variants have data. Stabilize const_ptr_offset_from. Stabilize generic associated types Uplift the let_underscore lints from clippy into rustc. Don’t derive PartialEq::ne. consider unnormalized types for implied bounds Update to LLVM 15 Do not allow Drop impl on foreign fundamental types Add armv4t-none-eabi take2 Stabilize std::io::read_to_string Stringify non-shorthand visibility correctly Update the minimum external LLVM to 13 Sunset RLS Don’t duplicate file descriptors into stdio fds Normalize struct field types in confirm_builtin_unsize_candidate
